**CRITICAL**: Always follow these naming conventions when creating ANY database object (tables, functions, procedures, packages, views, triggers, sequences, etc.)

#### ‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: New Objects Only Rule

**For NEW database objects created from 2025-11-14 onwards:**

**Always Check Before Creating Tables this database table check workflow**, refer to the [Database table check workflow] (,/database_table_check_workflow.md)

- ‚úÖ **MUST** use feature/module grouping with prefixes
- ‚úÖ **MUST** follow the complete naming pattern: `{scope}_{feature}_{object_name}_{suffix}`

**For EXISTING database objects:**

- ‚ö†Ô∏è **MAY** remain as-is (grandfathered)
- ‚ö†Ô∏è **WILL** be migrated gradually per migration plan
- ‚úÖ **MUST** use new naming when creating related objects

**‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: Existing Objects Reference**

**For EXISTING database objects**, refer to the [Grandfathered Objects Registry](./database_grandfathered_objects.md) for exact names.

**Key Points:**

- ‚úÖ Existing objects use old naming (without feature grouping)
- ‚úÖ Use exact names from the registry when referencing existing objects
- ‚úÖ Do NOT use feature-grouped names for existing objects (they don't exist)
- ‚úÖ When creating NEW related objects, use new naming convention

**Example:**

```sql
